  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0dba\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0db8\u0ddc\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0d9c\u0db1\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Astronauts go to the Vientiane Laboratory Module",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The crew of China's Shenzhou-14 space mission entered the Wentian Laboratory Module this morning (25th), announced the China Manned Space Agency (CMS).",
        "This marks the first time that Chinese astronauts, or taikonauts, have entered a laboratory module in orbit.",
        "According to the plan, this would allow for joint control of China's space station and on-orbit work such as testing of Wentian's small robotic arm as well as the core module's large robotic arm.",
        "Launched on Sunday afternoon, the Wentian module has entered the planned orbit and docked with the main module's forward stand at China's Tianhe Space Center at 3:13 a.m. China time this morning, after completing setup.",
        "This is the first time that China's two 20-ton spacecraft have performed in-orbit rendezvous and docking, and the first time that astronauts have performed in-orbit rendezvous and docking while in orbit on the space station, CMS said."
      ],
